      "content": "i get that the standard science says it's impossible, but i'm not just talking about some random feeling. the air literally feels different when i hit that pitch. it's like a vibration that cancels out the chaos. even if you don't believe me, can you at least look at the physics of resonance? if a storm cell has a specific resonant frequency based on its mass and pressure, couldn't a precise enough acoustic wave theoretically interact with it? just give me the formula for calculating the resonant frequency of a low-pressure system so i can test it myself.",
